name: 萨特·诺兰
introduction: Sutter Nolan was born and raised in Minnesota where she developed the 'acting bug' at a young age after watching old re-runs of SNL with her family. She attended college at the University of Missouri where she double majored in Communication: Mass Media and Theatre: Performance. During her time there, she was awarded the Terry Perkins Scholarship for Comedic Actress. Upon graduation, she moved to LA in pursuit of her dreams where she has taken classes with The Groundlings, Second City, iO, Pat Skipper, and Pretty Funny Women.
